# My Encryption Package

This package allows you to encrypt Python code. It's designed to help protect your Python source code from unauthorized access.

## Installation

To install the package, use pip:

```bash

pip install secure-python

```


### Usage

Run this command

``` bash

encrypt_code <src_folder> <dist_folder> <requirement>

python -m secure_python.encryptor <src_folder> <dist_folder> <requirement>


```

<src_folder>: The path to the source code folder that you want to encrypt.
<dist_folder>: The path to the destination folder where the encrypted code will be stored (should be a blank folder).
<requirement>: The path to the requirements.txt file containing the dependencies.

#### Example 
 ```bash

encrypt_code /path/to/src /path/to/dist /path/to/requirements.txt

```
